						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Okk wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Switching palette colors would compromise one of my scanlines with a rainbow of colors; I was wondering just what that would look like.<br /></div>I think you should be able to update up to 6 palette entries without any visible rainbow of colors.<br /><br />If you want to see what the spray of colors looks like, in its most extreme form, the demo Tepples mentioned by ccovell (Sayoonara!) is <a href="https://github.com/christopherpow/nes-test-roms/blob/master/other/Sayoonara!.NES" class="postlink">here</a>. But as tepples also mentioned, it's mostly invisible because ccovell uses the greyscale bit in the NES, which converts all 54 colors to one of three greys.<br /><span style="font-size: 50%; line-height: normal"><br />edit: grammar</span></div>

					
